    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@oskarth historically we have had issues with connection drops, as if you get disconnected from a mailserver/waku node while you are syncing messages, you have to start from scratch, leading to fetching the same messages multiple times.\r\n\r\nThis is technically correct, as mailserver don't have a synchronization protocol and therefore they are not consistent which each others, so attempting to use the same cursor across them is not something we want to use, it does work now, but there's no guarantee that it will in the future (think of a stateful cursor a la elasticsearch).\r\n\r\nThis is not necessarily  something we should lump in the same category as \"bandwidth improvements\" (no opinion on the matter), but I think it's something we should be doing in any case.",
